📘 Definition:
Tests are assessments used to check a candidate’s skills, knowledge, personality, or suitability for a job.

🎯 Purpose:
To collect measurable information about a candidate so employers can compare applicants fairly.

🧠 Types of Tests:

Aptitude Tests – Check logical thinking, math ability, and language skills.

Technical Tests – Test job-related knowledge or practical skills.

Personality Tests – Measure behavior, attitude, and cultural fit.

Psychometric Tests – Mix of cognitive (thinking) and personality checks.

Situational Judgment Tests (SJT) – Give scenarios to test decision-making and ethics.

📌 Importance:

Provide fair and standard results.

Reduce bias in hiring.

Save time when many candidates apply.

---

🗣️ Interviews in the Selection Process

📘 Definition:
An interview is a formal meeting between employer and candidate to judge qualifications, personality, and job suitability.

🎯 Purpose:
To know the candidate’s experience, communication, attitude, and values.

🔍 Types of Interviews:

Structured – Same set of questions for all candidates.

Unstructured – Free and conversational style.

Panel – Multiple interviewers together.

Behavioral – Based on past experiences.

Technical – Focused on job-related knowledge.

🧩 Good Interview Elements:

Clear goals and criteria.

Professional and respectful tone.

Open-ended questions.

Active listening and notes.

Fair and unbiased judgment.

---

🔗 Role of Tests & Interviews

Tests → give objective (measurable) data.

Interviews → give personal (qualitative) insights.
👉 Together, they make the selection process more accurate and fair.
